Computes the desired greek letter from Black-Scholes-Merton model.

Source: R/bsm.R
bsmgreeks.Rd

Greeks formula implementation, from Black-Scholes-Merton model.

Usage

bsmgreeks(
  greeks = c("delta", "gamma", "vega", "rho", "theta"),
  type,
  spot,
  strike,
  time,
  rate,
  yield,
  sigma
)

bsmdelta(type, spot, strike, time, rate, yield, sigma)

bsmvega(type, spot, strike, time, rate, yield, sigma)

bsmgamma(type, spot, strike, time, rate, yield, sigma)

bsmtheta(type, spot, strike, time, rate, yield, sigma)

bsmrho(type, spot, strike, time, rate, yield, sigma)

Arguments

greeks

desired greek letter: delta, gamma, vega, rho or theta.

type

call for call option, any other value for put.

spot

current stock price.

strike

the strike price.

time

time to option expiration in years.

rate

the risk-free interest rate.

yield

the dividends that are expected to be paid.

sigma

volatility of the stock price.

Value

Vector with desired greeks for input data.

Recycle rule

These arguments handle the recycle rule so vectors can be provided and once those vectors differs in length the recycle rule is applied.

bsmdelta

Delta greek letter measures the rate of change of the theoretical option value with respect to changes in the underlying asset's price.

bsmvega

Vega greek letter measures sensitivity of volatility.

bsmgamma

Gamma greek letter measures the rate of change in the delta with respect to changes in the underlying price.

bsmtheta

Theta measures the sensitivity of the value of the derivative to the passage of time.

bsmrho

Rho measures sensitivity to the interest rate: it is the derivative of the option value with respect to the risk free interest rate.

Examples

bsmgreeks("delta", "put", 20, 30, 0:2000 / 1000, 0.15, 0, 0.25)
